# DEVICE TAXONOMY - CONDENSED

Identify 15-20 literary devices with quoted examples from the text.

## DEVICE LIST (50+ devices available)

### NARRATIVE STRUCTURE
1. Linear Chronology - Events in temporal order
2. Non-Linear Chronology - Flashbacks/flashforwards
3. Frame Narrative - Story within story
4. In Medias Res - Starting mid-action
5. Circular/Spiral Structure - Returns to beginning
6. Episodic Structure - Loosely connected events

### NARRATIVE VOICE
7. First-Person Narration - "I" narrator
8. Third-Person Omniscient - All-knowing narrator
9. Third-Person Limited - One character's perspective
10. Unreliable Narrator - Compromised credibility
11. Free Indirect Discourse - Character thoughts in third person
12. Stream of Consciousness - Unfiltered thought flow
13. Second-Person Narration - "You" protagonist

### TEMPORAL MANIPULATION
14. Foreshadowing - Hints of future events
15. Flashback (Analepsis) - Return to past
16. Flashforward (Prolepsis) - Jump to future
17. Scene - Detailed moment
18. Summary - Compressed time
19. Pause - Descriptive/commentary
20. Ellipsis - Time gaps

### FIGURATIVE LANGUAGE
21. Metaphor - Direct comparison
22. Simile - Comparison with "like/as"
23. Personification - Human traits to non-human
24. Hyperbole - Exaggeration
25. Understatement/Litotes - Deliberate underemphasis
26. Symbolism - Object representing concept
27. Allegory - Extended metaphor
28. Motif - Recurring element

### IRONY
29. Verbal Irony - Says opposite of meaning
30. Situational Irony - Outcome opposite of expectation
31. Dramatic Irony - Reader knows more than character
32. Structural Irony - Sustained ironic framework

### SOUND DEVICES
33. Alliteration/Assonance/Consonance - Sound repetition
34. Rhythm/Meter - Pattern of stressed syllables
35. Onomatopoeia - Sound words

### SYNTACTIC DEVICES
36. Parallelism - Repeated grammatical structure
37. Anaphora - Repeated word/phrase at start
38. Epistrophe - Repeated word/phrase at end
39. Chiasmus - Inverted parallel structure
40. Polysyndeton - Repeated conjunctions
41. Asyndeton - Omitted conjunctions

### STRUCTURAL DEVICES
42. Juxtaposition - Contrasting elements side-by-side
43. Paradox - Contradictory truth
44. Oxymoron - Contradictory terms together

### META-NARRATIVE
45. Metafiction - Self-aware fiction
46. Breaking Fourth Wall - Direct address to reader
47. Unreliable Chronology - Time itself is unreliable

### RHETORICAL DEVICES
48. Apostrophe - Address to absent/abstract
49. Rhetorical Question - Question for effect
50. Ethos Establishment - Credibility building

## OUTPUT FORMAT

For each device identified, provide:
```json
{
  "device_name": "Metaphor",
  "classification": "B|Me|V",
  "quote_snippet": "exact quote from text (10-30 words)",
  "analysis": "brief explanation of function",
  "location": "chapter/page reference"
}
```

Identify 15-20 devices minimum. Include diverse device types across categories.
